Why is this important

Applications that specify or rely on binary dependencies that are no longer included in the buildpack will fail to deploy.

Existing applications that were deployed using a previous buildpack version and specify or depend on binary dependencies that are no longer included will continue to run but will fail to re-deploy.

A typical example of an error message in this situation is as follows:
Could not get translated url, exited with: 
DEPENDENCY_MISSING_IN_MANIFEST: https://path/to/ruby-2.1.0.tgz 

What you should do

If your application specifies or depends on a binary dependency that is supported in the new buildpack versions listed above, you do not need to take any further action.

If your application specifies or depends on a binary dependency that is no longer supported, please refer to this knowledge base article <http://www.google.com/url?q=http%3A%2F%2Fsupport.run.pivotal.io%2Fentries%2F82311705-What-runtime-language-and-server-versions-are-support-for-a-build-pack-&sa=D&sntz=1&usg=AFQjCNGnGGWIDAcviC8wgayuOZW1krZduQ> for instructions.

Please contact support@run.pivotal.io <mailto:support@run.pivotal.io> if you have any questions.

